Got BDE?⚡️
If you wanna support my newsletter, please CLICK HERE [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4f7369a-c605-4e1a-8eaa-690674bd7a4c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]🔗 to learn about my sponsor, Zapier, and how it connects to Snowflake ❤️
Hot take: If you’re in tech and NOT automating your workflows with AI by now, you’re working harder than you need to!!
In only a few years, we’ve gone from thinking, “AI chatbots are kind of cool, I guess,” to using AI daily and setting up automated systems to make our work and personal lives run more smoothly.
I love using AI to help me code as a data analyst, but I honestly love it EVEN MORE for my mission-critical work. I recently used Zapier [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4f7369a-c605-4e1a-8eaa-690674bd7a4c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] to automate the process of consolidating my email subscribers from multiple platforms into one place. Zapier🔗 [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4f7369a-c605-4e1a-8eaa-690674bd7a4c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] is the BEST AI orchestration platform to streamline processes and make things happen automatically behind the scenes— helping you be even more efficient.
Zapier integrates with tools like Gmail, Google Sheets, Slack, Notion, ChatGPT, and MORE (like 8,000 more)! And they now have Agents🔗 [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4f7369a-c605-4e1a-8eaa-690674bd7a4c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] to help automate your tasks, so you can get started today. Thanks Zapier [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4f7369a-c605-4e1a-8eaa-690674bd7a4c?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ] for sponsoring this newsletter :)
And subscribe on YouTube 🎥 [ https://substack.com/redirect/9577f8c6-5b42-458f-ad3d-e30c629f7b6e?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]— Just hit 9K subs 🎉 let’s get to 10K by next week 👀
And BIG announcement… I’m moving my courses to Kajabi to provide an even better user experience!! 🥳 I’m also planning some big, BIG Black Friday deals! Reply to this email on what you wanna see 👀
Why Negotiating is LIFE Altering 💰
Something about me is that I LOVE negotiating. The first time I did it, I didn’t know how! And I was so nervous and unsure of myself. I remember I asked many mentors and friends for advice on what to say and how to word it. And shockingly, I was successful! You’d be surprised about what you can get just for asking for more— so ALWAYS ask.
I increased my salary from $72K to $153K in the span of 11 months by living by these principles.
Negotiating isn’t just to have a little cash in the next year or so— it literally affects your whole entire life and can make a difference on when you retire. 
Understanding WHY negotiating matters so much makes it easier.
Many benefits and increases are based on your salary such as 401K % match, an annual % raise, and a % bonus. If you don’t negotiate that extra 10-20% of your salary, that will trickle down into all of your benefits and future increases costing you a LOT of money over time. Especially when we’re talking about investments that will compound annually over potentially 40 years (hello 401Ks!) that is a LOT of money you’re missing out on. It’s not just about the immediate cash, the effects COMPOUND over time.
If you negotiate, you’ll likely make more at your next job too. If you work somewhere for $100K and don’t negotiate, you may get a few raises and/or promotions and then be able to shoot for $130-150K at your next job. But if you work somewhere and negotiate the $100K to $120K, you’re in a much higher position after a few raises & promos. And you’ll likely be more confident and have more negotiation leverage at your next job too! Set yourself up with confidence for your next step.
The earlier on in your career you negotiate, the BETTER. I know so many people that start out at lower data analyst salaries ($55-70K) and remain complacent for years with their small increases. (BTW there’s nothing wrong with this if you’re happy! Just trying to help everyone get paid their worth and get PAID!) But I also have friends (and myself) who have negotiated every job offer, raise, and promo and are now making well over $100K just a few years into their careers. The gains in the first 5-10 years of your career are likely going to be larger than later on in your career, so you want to make sure you climb and maximize your potential as quickly as you can. Especially since time is of the essence for investing (look back at #1!).
If you’re a woman or BIPOC, chances are that negotiation is even MORE important for your career. Women and BIPOC are statistically paid less than their opposing counterparts (and a lot of times also lack the resources and support to know to negotiate but that’s a whole other topic!), so it’s especially vital to make sure we’re paid the same as others in our roles. Don’t let them lowball you and don’t accept less than you’re worth (know your market value!). But of course, negotiation is only half of the battle as the gender gap increases this year [ https://substack.com/redirect/6e81cb0e-8f9b-4e4b-8a49-4ae6fc1d6847?j=eyJ1IjoiNTFkc2s3In0.TG_s5GaRal_EYLFDF-UYKHL5eEiDcX8TdL6-5nynlYA ]🔗.
The best time to negotiate is when starting a new role. You’ll NEVER have more leverage to negotiate than when you’re first joining the company. If they already have you working there for X salary, they might not be willing to give you raise— after all, they already have you! But when you’re fresh meat and a new and exciting candidate, they may be more willing to tap into their budget a little more to get you to sign. So negotiate coming on even if you’re happy with your offer because it’s the most power and leverage you’ll EVER have at that company.
In addition to #5— job hopping allows you to be in the place of power and leverage more often, so you’re able to increase your salary greatly in a short amount of time (even in only a few years). Every time you start a new job, you’ll likely be able to swing a 20-30% increase (or maybe even more if you play your cards right). Multiply these increases over the course of your career and BOOM! Also add in the increased impact to your 401K and % raises, and you’re in the best spot possible. I’m team job hopper. Money isn’t the most important thing, but let’s be honest— we’re not out here working for fun!
Have you negotiated before? If so, how’d it go? If not, what’s stopping you?
Bye BDEs 💅🏼
Jess Ramos 💕

column7: Before you get your book, I wanted to share this...
column9:
Ever lost a client to a competitor you know has an inferior product to you? 
Candace,

‘We’ve decided to work with another supplier’.

Ouch.

Being replaced sucks (yeah I’ve been there too).

It really isn't fun when you know you have a better product or service…

My company Dent
[https://pu693.keap-link020.com/v2/click/da3a71108a9f220a52710c084ba04322/eJyNj00LgkAURf_LW0t-S81ORGTQXEStQ5yBhnQcxjeBiP-9scJVQdt3zz2POwNy2UikDAgokxxCcEDzVijBJWaDxKZ9hUngJYEDnZD3Qg9GAZm_Vbd8vfqhH3sO4KS4Rc6nNCtpXVwrWpcWVY22L_7xhEEU76NNlB9TWsGy_DTzXmD-sPIRCGrD10VM2FV40Z3lb4hqJK7LLLJrh743UuBki41SXLLP6pJP7_ryBDTkXtk=] 
has worked with thousands of established entrepreneurs, to help them unpack and
package the IP so they stand out and get noticed in their industry.

Each of these entrepreneurs became the Key People of Influence for what they do.

When you become one, your customers start to see you as a vital life force in
their life, not a functional supplier.

Vital people add something a functional person doesn’t have.

Functional is...

 * Great at what you do
 * Talk the talk and walk the walk
 * But at the end of the day…. you are performing a role for your customer that
   is replaceable.

If someone can find a cheaper option, they will take it.

A client can replace a functional supplier. An investor can easily put their
money into someone else.

Functional does the job but functional is still interchangeable.

The word vital has 2 components to its meaning: “irreplaceable” and the other is
“life-force”.

Vital people are the “irreplaceable life-force” of a project, a business, an
industry or even a cause.

They see themselves as redefining the game in some way.

They have their own unique take on things that makes them almost impossible to
overlook.

What do you want to become the irreplaceable life force in? What do you want to
be known for in your industry?

Hit reply, I’d love to know!

Cheers,

Hi there!

Innovation is in the core of HeyGen’s DNA. This month, we launched powerful upgrades to your favorite tools. Scroll down to see how we’re making voice design even better, utilize new advanced avatars, and check out HeyGen Mobile 1.5.

Voice Design Generation

Create lifelike, unique voices with just a text prompt. Yes, that's right. Simply describe the tone, pitch, emotion, or accent and our advanced AI brings it to life. We suggest prompting gruff, scary pirates and gentle pixies to get started, but something tells us that won't fit your video... Or maybe it will? It's your choice.

Creating a successful business is about managing energy—knowing where to focus and where to pull back can drive growth. In this week’s edition of AI Simplified, we explore how cultivating the right energy within your team fuels progress. From China’s groundbreaking Manus AI agent taking over autonomous tasks to Google’s AI Mode making search smarter, there’s no shortage of excitement in the AI space. Plus, discover Cortical Labs’ first-ever living biocomputer, a breakthrough in merging biology and technology.

In Today’s AI Simplified:

-

Founder’s Insight: Evaluate activities through energy ROI—boost with transparency and strong team-building.

-

AI News: China’s Manus transforms autonomous AI, Google AI Mode enhances search, and Cortical Labs unveils living biocomputer CL1.

-

AI Spotlights: Try Blackbox AI for coding, Sam Altman’s subscription credit idea, and the AI for Business free course.

In physics, energy is a fundamental concept—kinetic, potential, chemical, and more. In our company, we took concept of energy and made it measure of company's culture.

Some people add energy to the company. Some consume it. The same applies to processes and decisions.

How Energy Flows in a Company

✅ Energy-Boosting Activities

• All-hands meetings

• Transparency

• Strong team-building

• Celebrating wins

❌ Energy-Draining Activities

• Internal politics

• Poor performance

• Firing decisions

Some of these activities can’t be avoided, but we always evaluate them through the lens of ROI on energy.

💡 The biggest energy booster? Business success—winning new logos, increasing revenue, and achieving growth.

On the evening of March 6, in Shenzhen, a group of software engineers were testing Manus, an AI system that would shake the world. Manus is a fully autonomous AI agent that doesn’t just assist—it replaces human effort entirely. The world’s first of its kind, Manus performs tasks across industries without human oversight, making decisions with unparalleled speed and precision.

The "Second DeepSeek Moment"

This development comes shortly after China's DeepSeek V3 AI model, which was hailed as a competitor to OpenAI's GPT-4. Manus is a reasoning model that surpasses previous AI models, marking a major milestone in autonomous AI technology.

Manus initiates tasks and dynamically adjusts its approach. Imagine giving Manus a set of resumes—it doesn’t just rank them, it reads, analyzes, and generates an optimized decision on its own.

It operates using a multi-agent architecture, allowing it to break down complex tasks. This enables Manus to perform tasks like generating research papers, designing marketing campaigns, and building entire websites without human intervention.

Currently, Manus is available only to selected testers. The potential is clear: Manus represents the future of AI—autonomous and general-purpose.

Google Search Gets Smarter with ‘AI Mode’ Expansion (https://d2thJ004.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/2N+113/d2thJ004/VVvQ_d2TqqxjW5-FJqY4HFJsCW8wLjj95t1q13N6hnpq63pyd0W8wLKSR6lZ3nBW5DytTn1zHDzBW26ByV461sv7sW5zyLBs3mfM4kW69MLj06Zj-DJVw56JR2zhG_zN1R9KvzmDRwFN2QjvmRvkhh4W8KYfRn2TnL-7W68FPyg7BQBMRW5nqt4N21c29HVz8T4C97nG5PW6_1qZb8yfrT3V7BMPm824Zt0W3S_kD840H7fkW858ftK4hkc6rW5g7sC44pKpvfVgPjqg7w0V43W1Xh01b2zhc2TW1HvKdD4P3ckNW2dt5wP4d6lHCW8XPNn27kPllSW35dlp44q_M_6W6fBKwb634TMTVjS7vB7ypc9dW84NNYx8ZgW5mW8KN3dv3VBF--W6ZXNCq5q_4WGW4ZZ67h29TPJ1d3800j04 )

Google is rolling out major updates to its AI-powered search capabilities, including an expansion of AI Overviews and the introduction of AI Mode in Search. These features leverage the Gemini 2.0 model to enhance search experiences with deeper reasoning and real-time data retrieval.

Key Highlights:

- AI Overviews are now powered by Gemini 2.0 in the U.S., delivering faster and more precise responses for coding, advanced math, and multimodal queries.
- AI Mode, an experimental feature in Labs, expands AI-generated responses for complex, multi-step queries with advanced reasoning.
- Google One AI Premium subscribers will be the first to test AI Mode, with broader rollout plans coming soon.

Smarter Search with AI Mode

With AI Mode, users can ask intricate, multi-part questions—such as comparing sleep tracking devices—and receive comprehensive, AI-generated insights. The system uses a “query fan-out” technique, issuing multiple searches simultaneously to aggregate the most relevant information.

Google emphasizes that AI Mode is built on its core ranking systems, ensuring users can still access high-quality web content. Early testing has shown improvements in speed, accuracy, and factual consistency.

Cortical Labs has introduced the CL1, the world’s first deployable biological computer, integrating living neurons with silicon for real-time computation. Priced at $35,000, it offers a revolutionary step toward AI systems that more closely mimic human intelligence.

-

Living Neurons + Silicon: The CL1 connects biological neurons to a simulated environment using Cortical Labs' biOS, enabling real-time interaction.

-

Next-Gen AI Potential: Unlike traditional AI, which struggles with reasoning and hallucinations, this Synthetic Biological Intelligence (SBI) self-programs and evolves.

-

Future Expansion: Cortical Labs plans to develop biological neural network server stacks, making the technology more accessible via cloud computing.

💡 Will the CL1 redefine the future of computing the way Apple’s Lisa paved the way for modern interfaces? Only time will tell.
